# SAM Project: Skills and Jobs

The SAM (Student AI Mentor) project is actively seeking skilled individuals to join the team and contribute to the development of an advanced AI-based learning assistant for Vietnamese high school students.

## Hiring Requirements

We are looking for candidates with both technical capabilities and soft skills. The project aims to establish an AI assistant, follow a three-month development schedule, gather essential data, and build the required AI models.

## Current Positions

The SAM project currently has the following positions:

1. **Project Manager**: Responsible for project oversight, idea generation, and technical guidance.
2. **Quality Tester**: Ensures the consistency and quality of the system.
3. **Technical Advisor**: Offers guidance on technical functions and innovations.

## Open Positions

We are actively recruiting for the following positions:

### Back-end Developer

As a back-end developer, you will be responsible for:

- Designing and implementing the server and database structure.
- Selecting and configuring the appropriate technological stack.
- Creating and managing application programming interfaces (APIs).
- Developing storage and acceptance solutions, especially for payment processing.
- Writing, testing, and maintaining development solutions.

**Desired Skills:**

- Strong understanding of performance requirements and objectives.
- Experience in building high-efficiency solutions.
- Familiarity with DevOps practices.
- Proficiency in creating APIs.

### Data Analyst

As a data analyst, you will be responsible for:

- Translating raw data into logical insights.
- Ensuring accuracy and quality of core data.
- Cleaning and rearranging data for readability.
- Utilizing statistical methods to identify patterns and trends in complex data sets.

**Desired Skills:**

- Proficiency in data analytics tools such as R, Python, and SQL.
- Strong communication and presentation skills.

### AI Software Engineer

As an AI software engineer, you will be responsible for:

- Testing and qualifying AI models (machine learning, deep learning).
- Productizing data science research for internal or external stakeholders.
- Building Infrastructure as Code.
- Continuous Integration and Versioning Control.
- API Development.
- Development of Pilots and MVP Applications.

**Desired Skills:**

- Experience in software engineering with a focus on AI and machine learning.
- Strong problem-solving skills and ability to work under pressure.

## Joining the Team

If you are passionate about technology, education, and possess the skills required for any of the open positions, we would love to hear from you! Join us in building an advanced AI-based learning assistant to empower high school students in Vietnam.

To apply, please contact us at [your-email@example.com](mailto:your-email@example.com) with your resume and a brief introduction.

